data.description: This charming cape cod is located in the heart of Plain City just minutes from the brand new elementary school! The welcoming brick exterior makes for nearly maintenance free living and adds to the curb appeal of this home. The wrought iron details on the front porch carry over into the home. Many updates have been made, but the mid century charm remains. Originals and gleaming hardwood floors, wrought iron rails, glass door knobs, arched entries and solid wood doors and trim are just a few of the details that can be found in this home. Updates include lighting, electrical, kitchen, bathroom, carpet, insulated windows, garage roof, furnace, air conditioner, hot water tank, and appliances. When you enter the home you will be greeted by the "pottery barn" style that will make you feel right at home. The living/dining space is a cozy spot that easily allows for extra space when entertaining since both rooms flow into one another. The kitchen is fully applianced and it's updates make is a fun place for the cook in the family. The laundry area is conveniently located ont he first floor. The full bath on the main level has been updated. The current homeowners use the first floor bedroom as a home office, but this space could be a great first floor owners retreat. The upper level contains a nice landing area that could accomodate a nice built in office area and 2 very large bedrooms. The basement is neat and clean and is the perfect area for storage. Enjoy entertaining in the warmer months or just hanging outside in this well-sized and treed rear yard. The oversized garage is located just outside the back door to the home that leads to the kitchen for ease in unloading your grocercies. This home abounds with charm. Come see for yourself!!
